It was, easily, their worst loss of the year, and it couldn’t have come at a more inopportune time. They had their ace, James Shields, on the mound, and were playing in front of a sizable home crowd and commencing a crucial stretch in their postseason push: 15 straight games against opponents with better records. So, yes, awful.
